BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Preserve-a-Preserve: Weed Wrangle at Beanblossom Bottoms
DTSTART:20260528T100000
DTEND:20260528T120000
UID:01eaa224aa114933a787bfb02baa83b5@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Spend a day tromping through wetlands during our Beanblossom B
 ottoms Nature Preserve Weed Wrangle as we work together to remove invasive
  cattails. Over the past couple of years\, storms and tornado damage have 
 opened the canopy in parts of the preserve\, allowing more sunlight to rea
 ch the wetlands\, which causes aggressive species like cattails to spread.
  Participants will work off-trail in shallow water\, using cut-stump techn
 iques to target cattails to help restore native wetland vegetation. By red
 ucing cattail dominance\, we can improve habitat for birds\, amphibians\, 
 and aquatic invertebrates while supporting the wetland’s natural recover
 y after these landscape altering events.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/preserve-a-preserve-weed-wrangle
 -at-beanblossom-bottoms-2/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Free virtual lecture: The Lives and Times of Midwest Amphibians wi
 th Dr. Spencer Cortwright
DTSTART:20260528T190000
DTEND:20260528T203000
UID:98da05f623066c829b7ce3119d223c81@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Each spring amphibians bring great joy as they seem to suddenl
 y emerge from a frozen landscape. Join us for a free virtual lecture and Q
 &amp\;A with Dr. Spencer Cortwright\, Professor of Biology at Indiana Univ
 ersity Northwest and longtime researcher of amphibian and restoration ecol
 ogy. Dr. Cortwright will take us on a richly illustrated journey through t
 he lives of Midwestern amphibians\, exploring their year-round life cycles
 \, seasonal movements\, and the remarkable adaptations that help them tran
 sition from a frozen landscape to springtime abundance.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/the-lives-and-times-of-midwest-a
 mphibians-with-dr-spencer-cortwright/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Preserve-a-Preserve: Weed Wrangle at Beanblossom Bottoms
DTSTART:20260529T100000
DTEND:20260529T120000
UID:fc1577f498a9fdef7e6bfd83e8c66a09@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Spend a day tromping through wetlands during our Beanblossom B
 ottoms Nature Preserve Weed Wrangle as we work together to remove invasive
  cattails. Over the past couple of years\, storms and tornado damage have 
 opened the canopy in parts of the preserve\, allowing more sunlight to rea
 ch the wetlands\, which causes aggressive species like cattails to spread.
  Participants will work off-trail in shallow water\, using cut-stump techn
 iques to target cattails to help restore native wetland vegetation. By red
 ucing cattail dominance\, we can improve habitat for birds\, amphibians\, 
 and aquatic invertebrates while supporting the wetland’s natural recover
 y after these landscape-altering events.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/preserve-a-preserve-weed-wrangle
